1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Beneath our feet lies a hidden network, connecting life in unimaginable ways.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:11,200
Mycelium, the vast network of fungal threads, links trees and soil in a dance of survival.

3
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:17,200
This mycorrhizal network allows trees to share nutrients and even warn each other of danger.

4
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:20,400
But scientists debate the extent of this communication.

5
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,000
It’s not all clear-cut.

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:27,200
What’s undeniable is that mycelium supports ecosystems, playing a pivotal role in biodiversity.

7
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:30,000
Curious about the secrets beneath our forests?

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,400
Follow for more fascinating nature insights!
